NPT (no restraints, IOD, gAMD dual boost)
The simulation goes
1-- >  ++ntcmdprep (Eq) ----> ++ntcmd (collecting data for gAMD param) --> ++ntebprep (gAMD eq.) --> ++nteb (gAMD collecting
statistics for further gAMD parameterization) --> up to ntslim (production gAMD run) 

ntave: number of simulation steps used to calculate the average and standard deviation of potential energies.

It is recommended to be updated as about 4 times of the total number of atoms in the system.
Note that ntcmd and nteb need to be multiples of ntave
Present values adjusted for DUMMY_NAT atoms 

 &cntrl
   ntx=5, irest=1, ntxo=2, 
   ntc=2, ntf=2, tol=0.000001,
   nstlim=DUMMY_NTSLIM, 
   ntpr=500000, ntwx=50000,
   ntwr=500000, ioutfm=1, 
   dt=0.002, cut=9.,
   ntb=2, ntp=1, barostat=2, 
   temp0=300.0, ntt=3, ig=-1, gamma_ln=2.0,
   igamd = 3, iE = 1, irest_gamd = 0,
   ntcmdprep = DUMMY_NTCMDPREP, 
   ntcmd = DUMMY_NTCMD, 
   ntebprep = DUMMY_NTEBPREP,
   nteb = DUMMY_NTEB, 
   ntave = DUMMY_NTAVE,
